## Preliminary Method Plan

### 1. Data Cleaning
- Load Chicago neighborhood boundaries as an `sf` object in R
- Join tree canopy CSV data to neighborhood polygons by name
- Download CDC SVI at census-tract level and spatially join to neighborhoods 
- Extract mean land surface temperature per neighborhood from Landsat raster
- Pull ACS income and race/ethnicity data 

### 2. Variables

Response - Mean Land Surface Temperature in degrees celsius per neighborhood
Predictor 1 - Tree canopy coverage in percentage
Predictor 2 - Impervious Surface in percentage
Predictor 3 - Median Household Income in Dollars
Predictor 4 - Percentage of residents identifying as non-white

